# ── Setup ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to a new file named ".env" (in the same folder) and put your
# key in it. The server loads .env automatically on start — no shell export
# needed, works the same on Windows, macOS, and Linux.
#
#   Windows (PowerShell):  Copy-Item .env.example .env
#   macOS / Linux:         cp .env.example .env
#
# Then set ONE provider key below and run:  npm start

# ── Choose ONE AI provider (whichever key you set is used automatically) ──

# Option A — Google Gemini (from Google AI Studio: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey)
GEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash   # default; or gemini-2.5-pro

# Option B — Anthropic Claude (https://platform.claude.com)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# If BOTH keys are set, Gemini is used. Force a specific one with:
# AI_PROVIDER=gemini   # or: claude

# ── Optional server settings ──
# PORT=3000
# DB_FILE=./data/copilot.db   # history database location
# MOCK_MODE=1                 # run the full UI with canned responses, no API key needed
